Source:  NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page:  56/5/4
Edition:
Quote:  At the same time the practice rendered it unsafe for any girl to wait abroad for her legitimate lover or any wife for her husband. She was almost certain to be accosted by some prowling `masher"- a word that was in much more common use then than it is now - [20 years before] and cases of condign punishment for such audacity, at the hands of lover or husband, were so frequent as hardly to excite comment.
